Source: openmeteo
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Nikita Shkoda <nikita@lstpsche.dev>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/lstpsche/openmeteo
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: openmeteo
Architecture: all
Depends: bash (>= 4.0), jq, curl, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Fast, lightweight CLI for the entire Open-Meteo API suite
 A Bash CLI tool that provides access to all Open-Meteo APIs from the
 terminal: weather forecasts, historical data, ensemble models, climate
 projections, marine weather, air quality, flood data, elevation lookup,
 and satellite solar radiation.
 .
 Features human-friendly colored output, machine-parseable porcelain
 format, and raw JSON mode. Only requires jq as a non-standard dependency.
